hopobject.body: There's a three month trial period rejuvenem NEWS ITEM--A spate of five-figure water bills in an Ohio city is being blamed on new software, but a pastor jokes his church's $93,000 bill was from using too much holy water. The July bill sent to St. Rose Catholic Church in Girard was one of many erroneous statements sent to the city's water customers/ The Youngstown Vindicator reports that the Tri-Changes Hair Salon got a $12,000 bill.
